data.title: Ultima Markets and Inter deepen partnership in Milan, celebrating Regional Partnership for Asian territory, transitioning from online to real world.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Ultima Markets announced a new Regional Partnership for the Asian region with FC Internazionale Milano (Inter) in Milan. This collaboration marks a significant step as the two entities transitioned from an online connection to a physical presence in Milan. Passion, performance, and purpose converged as they solidified their partnership, enhancing opportunities in the Asian market.

data.title: Charter Communications expected to report higher Q3 earnings, with analysts forecasting $9.29 per share, lower revenue at $13.75B.
data.description: Charter Communications, Inc. (NASDAQ: CHTR) is set to announce its third-quarter earnings before markets open on Friday, Oct. 31. Analysts predict the Connecticut-based company will post earnings of $9.29 per share, up from $8.82 per share a year ago. Revenue for the quarter is expected to be around $13.75 billion, slightly less than the $13.79 billion reported in the previous year. In the second quarter, Charter Communications saw a 0.6% revenue growth, surpassing projections at $13.77 billion. Following this news, the company's stock price dropped by 4.4%, closing at $230.92 on Thursday. For more detailed information, including analyst ratings, interested readers can visit the Analyst Stock Ratings page on Benzinga.

data.title: Utenos Trikotažas sees 30.7% revenue growth to Eur 15.9 million in 2025, with exports contributing to 80.7% of sales.
data.description: Throughout the first three quarters of 2025, Utenos Trikotažas, a part of the SBA textile group, experienced ongoing expansion with its revenue surging by 30.7% to reach Eur 15.9 million. The majority of the sales, amounting to 80.7%, came from exports.

data.title: Vesper Bio reports >95% increase in progranulin levels with lead candidate VES001 for frontotemporal degeneration.
data.description: During a recent Phase Ib/IIa study, VES001, the inaugural oral treatment under examination for FTD, was discovered to result in a mean increase of over 95% in progranulin levels in cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) in comparison to the baseline. The topline findings of the study suggest that VES001 has the capability to restore progranulin levels in individuals experiencing a deficiency of this crucial protein due to genetic factors.

data.title: China leads in urban health-climate solutions with 8 of 13 indicators at record highs; paves way for global south.
data.description: The recently released Lancet Countdown China report indicates that 8 out of 13 climate-health risk indicators have reached their highest levels in history. The launch event in Beijing on October 31, 2025, highlighted scalable strategies for fostering resilient and low-carbon urban development. This report underscores the urgency of addressing these challenges, with numbers like eight out of thirteen indicators peaking, signaling the need for immediate action to combat climate-related health risks.

data.title: McKay Brothers gets minority investments from Optiver and Qube, announced on Oct. 31, 2025, for its financial data services.
data.description: In a recent press release date October 31, 2025, McKay Brothers, a prominent company based in Oakland, California, Chicago, Geneva, and Paris, shared that they have partnered with Optiver and Qube Research & Technologies (QRT). McKay Brothers, known for its expertise in sourcing and delivering financial data quickly and reliably between financial institutions, will be working alongside these entities to enhance their services further. The collaboration with Optiver and Qube Research & Technologies holds great promise, potentially impacting the financial industry with their combined resources.

data.title: Kalmar's Q3 2025 report shows record-high operating profit margin of 13.8%, with orders received at EUR 375 million, down 10%. Sales increased 3% to EUR 436 million, while profit for the period was EUR 45 million. Cash flow from operations was EUR 26 million. Orders for the period totaled EUR 1,306 million, an increase of 9%, with an order book of EUR 961 million. Operating profit in the period was EUR 160 million. Kalmar expects a comparable operating profit margin above 12% in 2025. The company emphasizes sustainability and innovation in its strategy for growth. Kalmar's vision includes targets for sales growth, comparable operating profit margin, ROCE, leverage, dividend payout ratio, and a commitment to the SBTi targets. The full article is available on Benzinga.com.
data.description: Kalmar Corporation released its interim report for January-September 2025, on October 31, 2025. The report highlights an improved profitability with a record-high comparable operating profit margin of 13.8%. Equipment orders received declined by 20% compared to the previous period, but year-to-date showed solid growth. In July-September 2025, orders received totaled EUR 375 million, down by 10%, while the order book stood at EUR 961 million. Sales increased by 3% to EUR 436 million. Operating profit was EUR 61 million, representing 13.9% of sales. Cash flow from operations was EUR 26 million. Profit for the period amounted to EUR 45 million. For January-September 2025, orders received increased by 9%, reaching EUR 1,306 million. Sales decreased by 2% to EUR 1,254 million. Operating profit was EUR 160 million, representing 12.8% of sales. Cash flow from operations was EUR 133 million, and profit for the period was EUR 118 million. The company expects its comparable operating profit margin to be above 12% for the year. Kalmar achieved various sustainability milestones and financial targets for 2028 include sales growth of 5% per annum, a 15% comparable operating profit margin, and a dividend payout ratio of 30-50% annually, among others. Kalmar is committed to sustainable innovations and operational excellence to drive profitability and growth.
